main event: A civilian woman observed an unidentified object in the sky near Palmer, Alaska on February 11, 1952.
interesting points: The object was first seen hovering, then slowly tilted and moved in a zig-zag course for several miles.
The object was hanging in the air for approximately 10 minutes before moving.
The object was described as an astronomical body with reflecting movement or light.
The sighting was confirmed by radar and military authorities were notified.
The object's nature and origin remained unidentified.
sighted object: an unidentified, saucer-like or circular object
photographs: no photographs present in the document
